   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "# Online News Popularity - Feature Engineering\n",
    "\n",
    "## Objective\n",
    "Transform raw features into more predictive ones through:\n",
    "1. Feature creation (combining, transforming, interacting)\n",
    "2. Handling multi-collinearity (dropping redundant features)\n",
    "3. Scaling features for modeling\n",
    "4. Preparing train/test splits\n",
    "\n",
    "## Why Feature Engineering Matters\n",
    "From our EDA, we found:\n",
    "- Individual feature correlations with shares are weak (max ~0.22)\n",
    "- Some features are redundant (kw_avg_avg ↔ kw_max_avg: 0.81)\n",
    "- Log transformation is needed for the target variable\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### Setup and Initial Feature Engineering"
   ],
   "id": "7b92359548dc1239"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2026-06-20T08:45:53.559461Z",
     "start_time": "2026-06-20T08:45:53.220361Z"
    }
   },
   "cell_type": "code",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Original dataset shape: (39644, 61)\n",
      "After removing non-predictive columns: (39644, 59)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "execution_count": 1,
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression, Ridge, Lasso\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error, mean_absolute_error, r2_score\n",
    "import joblib\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set visualization style\n",
    "plt.style.use('seaborn-v0_8-whitegrid')\n",
    "sns.set_palette(\"husl\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load data\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv('../data/raw/OnlineNewsPopularity.csv')\n",
    "df.columns = df.columns.str.strip()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Original dataset shape: {df.shape}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Remove non-predictive columns\n",
    "df = df.drop(columns=['url', 'timedelta'])\n",
    "print(f\"After removing non-predictive columns: {df.shape}\")"
   ],
   "id": "943ebc4e039fa07d"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "### Feature Engineering",
   "id": "56017e8c8c26c732"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2026-06-20T08:45:55.252757Z",
     "start_time": "2026-06-20T08:45:55.201406Z"
    }
   },
   "cell_type": "code",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Features after engineering: 69\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "execution_count": 2,
   "source": [
    "# === 1. Media Features ===\n",
    "df['media_count'] = df['num_imgs'] + df['num_videos']\n",
    "df['has_media'] = (df['media_count'] > 0).astype(int)\n",
    "df['media_density'] = df['media_count'] / (df['n_tokens_content'] + 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "# === 2. Content Features ===\n",
    "df['content_length_per_href'] = df['n_tokens_content'] / (df['num_hrefs'] + 1)\n",
    "df['href_density'] = df['num_hrefs'] / (df['n_tokens_content'] + 1)\n",
    "df['self_reference_ratio'] = df['num_self_hrefs'] / (df['num_hrefs'] + 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "# === 3. Keyword Features ===\n",
    "df['keyword_score'] = df['kw_avg_avg'] * (df['kw_min_avg'] + df['kw_max_avg']) / 2\n",
    "\n",
    "# === 4. Topic Features ===\n",
    "topic_cols = ['LDA_00', 'LDA_01', 'LDA_02', 'LDA_03', 'LDA_04']\n",
    "df['topic_diversity'] = df[topic_cols].var(axis=1)\n",
    "df['dominant_topic'] = df[topic_cols].idxmax(axis=1).str.replace('LDA_', '').astype(int)\n",
    "\n",
    "# === 5. Sentiment Features ===\n",
    "df['sentiment_volatility'] = df['max_positive_polarity'] - abs(df['min_negative_polarity'])\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Features after engineering: {df.shape[1]}\")"
   ],
   "id": "c31d11bbd055b8f5"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "### Remove Redundant Features",
   "id": "dde736c48a1394fc"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2026-06-20T08:45:56.197784Z",
     "start_time": "2026-06-20T08:45:56.190786Z"
    }
   },
   "cell_type": "code",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Features after removing redundancy: 49\n",
      "\n",
      "Final features: ['n_tokens_title', 'n_tokens_content', 'n_non_stop_words', 'num_hrefs', 'num_self_hrefs', 'average_token_length', 'num_keywords', 'data_channel_is_lifestyle', 'data_channel_is_entertainment', 'data_channel_is_socmed', 'kw_avg_min', 'kw_min_max', 'kw_avg_max', 'self_reference_avg_sharess', 'weekday_is_monday', 'weekday_is_tuesday', 'weekday_is_wednesday', 'weekday_is_thursday', 'weekday_is_friday', 'weekday_is_saturday', 'is_weekend', 'LDA_00', 'LDA_01', 'LDA_03', 'LDA_04', 'global_subjectivity', 'global_sentiment_polarity', 'global_rate_negative_words', 'rate_negative_words', 'avg_positive_polarity', 'min_positive_polarity', 'max_positive_polarity', 'avg_negative_polarity', 'min_negative_polarity', 'max_negative_polarity', 'title_subjectivity', 'title_sentiment_polarity', 'abs_title_subjectivity', 'shares', 'media_count', 'has_media', 'media_density', 'content_length_per_href', 'href_density', 'self_reference_ratio', 'keyword_score', 'topic_diversity', 'dominant_topic', 'sentiment_volatility']\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "execution_count": 3,
   "source": [
    "# === Features to drop (highly correlated or redundant) ===\n",
    "features_to_drop = [\n",
    "    # Identical content features (keep only n_non_stop_words)\n",
    "    'n_unique_tokens', 'n_non_stop_unique_tokens',\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Original media features (replaced by media_count)\n",
    "    'num_imgs', 'num_videos',\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Redundant keyword features (keep keyword_score)\n",
    "    'kw_avg_avg', 'kw_min_avg', 'kw_max_avg', 'kw_max_min', 'kw_min_min', 'kw_max_max',\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Redundant LDA topics (keep LDA_03 which correlates best with shares)\n",
    "    'LDA_02',\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Redundant self-reference (keep only average)\n",
    "    'self_reference_min_shares', 'self_reference_max_shares',\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Redundant temporal (is_weekend captures this)\n",
    "    'weekday_is_sunday',\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Redundant channel features (LDA topics capture this better)\n",
    "    'data_channel_is_world', 'data_channel_is_bus', 'data_channel_is_tech',\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Redundant sentiment features\n",
    "    'rate_positive_words', 'global_rate_positive_words',\n",
    "    'sentiment_balance', 'sentiment_consistency',\n",
    "    'abs_title_sentiment_polarity',\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Keep only features that exist\n",
    "features_to_drop = [col for col in features_to_drop if col in df.columns]\n",
    "df = df.drop(columns=features_to_drop)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Features after removing redundancy: {df.shape[1]}\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nFinal features: {df.columns.tolist()}\")"
   ],
   "id": "e17f89ed6a9e31bb"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": "### Prepare Data for Modeling\n",
   "id": "5f342b034d652ca6"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2026-06-20T08:45:57.458620Z",
     "start_time": "2026-06-20T08:45:57.388281Z"
    }
   },
   "cell_type": "code",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "=== Data Preparation Summary ===\n",
      "Training samples: 31715\n",
      "Test samples: 7929\n",
      "Number of features: 48\n",
      "\n",
      "=== Top 15 Features by Correlation with Target ===\n",
      "  LDA_03                              0.1260\n",
      "  is_weekend                          0.1144\n",
      "  href_density                        0.1071\n",
      "  num_hrefs                           0.1051\n",
      "  media_count                         0.0990\n",
      "  self_reference_avg_sharess          0.0872\n",
      "  data_channel_is_entertainment       -0.0825\n",
      "  data_channel_is_socmed              0.0811\n",
      "  weekday_is_saturday                 0.0792\n",
      "  global_subjectivity                 0.0752\n",
      "  num_keywords                        0.0659\n",
      "  dominant_topic                      0.0636\n",
      "  kw_avg_max                          0.0597\n",
      "  keyword_score                       0.0553\n",
      "  content_length_per_href             -0.0543\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "execution_count": 4,
   "source": [
    "# === Separate features and target ===\n",
    "X = df.drop(columns=['shares'])\n",
    "y = df['shares']\n",
    "\n",
    "# Log transform target\n",
    "y_log = np.log1p(y)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Train-test split\n",
    "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(\n",
    "    X, y_log, test_size=0.2, random_state=42\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Scale features\n",
    "scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
    "X_train_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X_train)\n",
    "X_test_scaled = scaler.transform(X_test)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=== data Preparation Summary ===\")\n",
    "print(f\"Training samples: {X_train.shape[0]}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Test samples: {X_test.shape[0]}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Number of features: {X_train.shape[1]}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Check correlations with target\n",
    "print(\"\\n=== Top 15 Features by Correlation with Target ===\")\n",
    "correlations = []\n",
    "for col in X.columns:\n",
    "    corr = X[col].corr(y_log)\n",
    "    correlations.append((col, corr))\n",
    "correlations.sort(key=lambda x: abs(x[1]), reverse=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "for col, corr in correlations[:15]:\n",
    "    print(f\"  {col:35} {corr:.4f}\")"
   ],
   "id": "2d8ec130034f079c"
  },
